{"id": "1449157947665158256", "channel_id": "1449157947665158256", "type": 0, "author_id": "140102992035577856", "author_name": "pyros_", "author_bot": false, "content": "With the lastest major patch, the Curiculum premium track was upgraded to provide triple rewards from the daily which is nice. The problem is that bonus(along the ability to rewind turns and use everything in Traphase) is entirely tied to the duration of the battlepass. \n\nIf you buy it on the last day of the battlepass, ~~you literally get no benefit~~ edit: You do get the xp/standard pulls retroactively, but you don't get all the dream verves due to cap. If the battlepass is shortened(like the next one from dec 15th to dec 29th), then you simply get less days for the same price.\n\nI think instead of this system, it should provide something that works like the Moonphase Vigil(subscription) for a set number of days regardless of when you buy it. So you spend money on premium, you always get 28days of triple daillies/rewind/traphase unlocks. Doesn't matter when you buy it or how long the battlepass runs for, you always get 28days so the full value's worth, so it doesn't feel bad to spend on this upgrade if you don't buy it on day1 or if it's shortened.", "timestamp": "2025-12-12T21:56:18.776000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-15T06:54:32.399000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "☝️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 6}, {"emoji": "💯", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1449157947665158256", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Curiculum(Battle Pass) Premium rewards suggestion", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
